author: @kittyc997
text:
Did anyone else notice how FNF and DLC are exact opposites? FNF has such a happy and hopeful sound, but the words have such sadness. Then DLC has the happy and hopeful words, but the music has a darker, sadder feel. I love the contrast in each song, and then together they are the perfect complement. That Stray Kids depth and creativity always keep us coming back!
Also, FNF is such a perfect song for this album. After lots of hype and party songs (which I love), we can settle into a quieter hopeful song. So touching and sweet. The video always makes me smile, seeing all the members together.
Sending love to all the members, and all my STAY friends. ğŸ’•

author: @salathe-el
text: In 2019/2020 a bushfire storm in Australia destroyed 243,000 square kilometres of flora and fauna, which are the "ashes in the sky". That's an area about twice the size of South Korea. It was estimated that 3 billion animals were killed/affected, including some 60,000 koalas.This video was filmed in Melbourne Australia and you can see some of the type of flora which are typically Australian. The trees right at the start of eucalypts (gum trees) and are our beautiful native trees that grow everywhere. The section with Seungmin starting at 0.39 shows typical shrubs and the trees in the background at 1.36 are Norfolk Island pines.

author: @mustyrushroom7567
text: Seungmin's bike tire pops while he's riding it! I.N. offers his bubblegum as a temporary plug for the hole in the bike, and his skateboard as a temporary plug for the hole in Seungmin's heart. Lee Know finds a poster of a bike repair shop nearby. Felix reads "The Biker's Guide to Popped Tires" in hopes of finding anything helpful. Han opens a fortune cookie that reads, "Cherishing the fact that you can lose anything precious," and he thinks of Seungmin and his beloved bike. Meanwhile, Changbin listens to a bike owner podcast titled "The Cycle-ogical Impact of a Busted Bike" where other people talk about the emotional trauma and recovery of their popped bike tire, with this he might know how to comfort the heartbroken Seungmin. Hyunjin paints a picture of Seungmin's bike as a gift to Seungmin so that he can cherish his memories with his bike. And Bang Chan shows Seungmin that bikes aren't the only way to get around.

I'm forever thankful to have found yours.

author: @RM_formerlyjustRMbutYTsucks
text:
The more I listen to this, the more I appreciate the playing they did with the vocal elements. Felix's in particular really is standing out to me, but I like the smart way they set up the contrast between his voice and Hyunjin's/Lee Know's/Chris's and how that shows off all those other voices as well. Then the more set-aside calm(ish) rap section for 2RACHA and similar vocal section for Vocalracha.

Basically I just really like the overall composition of the song, the thoughtful way they put it together. The production is pleasantly simple, so the composition part of things stands out.

author: @beatriceoliverio5449
text:
I've been listening to some of your songs for a while now, but it wasn't to the point where I was really interested about the group. I fell in love with Bang Chan already, but for the others it was more like "Well, I like their music but I don't know them".
Yesterday I listened to your new album for the first time and I liked the music so much that my curiosity about the group and the courage to finally learn about them finally exploded in my heart.
I've started watching the elimination process from when you were still trainees and fell in love with the group. Even if I know who's now a part of it, I could still live the emotions you were going through during that time. Now (in the timeline I'm living in right now through the old videos) you've finally been announced as a 9 members group.
The happiness I felt and the pride I take in seeing you starting to bloom is so great.
So, even if it's a little confusing for my brain to keep switching from 2017 to 2023, I'm so happy to be able to listen to you, knowing your names, recognizing your faces and feeling your personality behind the character.
I'm very happy to finally be starting this journey.
I've been thinking about wanting to know you more for so long, so my heart is finally filled with joy now that I've begun my journey.
I'm learning so much and I'm so grateful for that.

Thank you for your hard work all this time.

I hope I'll get the hang of it soon so that I can finally enjoy your music at 100%.

For now, I'll just keep listening and looking forward to knowing all your songs by heart.

author: @dawnrose1971
text: I love the message behind this song. As an aussie this song hits close to home. The song was filmed in Australia and is a letter to all the hardships Australia experienced during the bushfires in 2019-20. Many people lost their homes, and a lot of native animals and plants were burnt. Literally up to 3 billion animals died, hence the title of the song 'FNF', flora and fauna. Based on what Chan and Felix explain, they made the song almost like losing or missing a loved one while also relating it to nature. This song is an anthem to all flora and fauna being lost throughout the world by world disasters.

author: @SJ-uc2rk
text:
It's very touching with the message to protect and love nature. Not only Australian wildfires, but also the climate crisis, and the wind that human-made disasters don't want to happen. I deeply sympathize with these lyrics... I can feel the ordinary daily life that I continue to see in the music video, and the preciousness of nature in it. It is also reminiscent of the opposition to the discharge of contaminated water from Fukushima, Japan. I hope this peaceful and ordinary daily life with nature will continue. Stay, please join forces. I hope you will speak out against the release of Fukushima contaminated water to protect the daily life of your loved ones, Stray Kids, and Stay.

Bangchan, thank you for making FNF. Stray Kids, let's protect this precious nature together... I love you stray kids & stay & FNF & earth
